-- H2O Innovation Wins Industrial, Municipal Water System Contracts
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-10T16:05:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/h2o-innovation-wins-industrial-municipal-water-system-contracts.html
H2O Innovation Inc. (HEO) , a Canadian
designer of custom-built water treatment systems, said it was
awarded C$6.5 million ($6.6 million) in contracts for municipal
and industrial users in the U.S. and Canada.  The contracts bring to $20.4 million the company’s water-
treatment system order backlog, it said today in a statement
from  Quebec City . The contracts include work on a drinking water
production system in Delaware, Ohio, another in Snow Lake,
Manitoba, a third in Grover, Colorado, a reclamation of
wastewater project in Idaho and a drinking water production
system to a Canadian oil and gas customer that wasn’t
identified.  To contact the reporter on this story:
